videos.description: Oklahoma State's Justice Hill runs in to a wall and coughs up the football, leading to a West Virginia recovery.
videos.headline: Cowboys turn it over on second play

videos.description: Oklahoma State backup RB J.D. King loses the handle and fumbles the ball, which gets scooped up by the Mountaineers.
videos.headline: Cowboys fumble on second possession

videos.description: The next play after recovering a fumble, Will Grier throws an interception up the middle of the field to give the ball back to Oklahoma State.
videos.headline: West Virginia gives it right back

videos.description: A quick slant route from Mason Rudolph to James Washington ends up in a touchdown, giving the Cowboys an early lead.
videos.headline: Okla. St. on the board first

videos.description: Mason Rudolph charges up the middle for the 1-yard score.
videos.headline: Cowboys add rushing TD

videos.description: The ball gets poked out of the hands of West Virginia's Justin Crawford and Oklahoma State's Taaj Bakari is there to jump on it.
videos.headline: Mountaineers put the ball on the ground

videos.description: Following a fumble, J.D. King sidesteps and finds a hole to run it in from 20 yards out.
videos.headline: Cowboys boost their lead with 2nd rushing TD

videos.description: Kennedy McKoy struggles with the handoff from Will Grier, but hangs on for the touchdown.
videos.headline: West Virginia scores rushing TD before halftime

videos.description: Cowboys head coach Mike Gundy wants to keep the ball on the ground and doesn't  think the wet weather will be a factor in the second half.
videos.headline: Okla. St. Coach Gundy wants to run the ball more

videos.description: Mountaineers head coach Dana Holgorsen needed the offense to get a boost at the end of the half and got it with the rushing touchdown.
videos.headline: WVU coach Holgorsen needed the late TD

videos.description: Mason Rudolph's touchdown pass to J.D. King in the third quarter makes Rudolph the school's all-time leader in passing touchdowns.
videos.headline: TD pass gives Rudolph Oklahoma State record

videos.description: La'Darren Brown can't handle the toss from Mason Rudolph and the fumble is recovered by West Virginia's David Long Jr.
videos.headline: Okla. St. botches toss and turns it over

videos.description: Oklahoma State's Jerel Morrow grabs Will Grier's errant pass and returns the interception 20 yards.
videos.headline: West Virginia turns it over for the 4th time

videos.description: Oklahoma State lines up  for the PAT, but the ball is mishandled by the holder, leading to a failed attempt.
videos.headline: Oklahoma State has Charlie Brown moment on PAT

videos.description: Osman Kamara races around the line to block the punt in the end zone and the Mountaineers recover for the touchdown.
videos.headline: West Virginia blocks punt and scores TD

videos.description: Mason Rudolph rolls out and forces a pass that gets intercepted by Kenny Robinson, who returns it 39 yards for a Mountaineers touchdown to cut Oklahoma State's lead to 30-24.
videos.headline: West Virginia keeps up pressure with huge pick-six

videos.description: The Mountaineers score off a blocked punt and then add another touchdown with a pick-six under a minute later to cut into Oklahoma State's lead.

tracking.trackingName: NCF_One-Play (West Virginia scores twice in 50 seconds to cut deficit) 2017/10/28 ESHEET

videos.headline: West Virginia scores twice in 50 seconds to cut deficit

videos.description: Justice Hill runs to the outside, side-steps on a dime to avoid the defenders and score the touchdown.
videos.headline: Nice juke move leads to Okla. St. rushing TD

videos.description: Coming into this game, Will Grier had only thrown 8 interceptions in his career. This is his fourth interception today.
videos.headline: Grier throws fourth INT

videos.description: After great field position from the interception, Mason Rudolph connects with James Washington for the 19-yard touchdown.
videos.headline: Oklahoma State scores following INT

videos.description: Will Grier tosses it up for Marcus Simms who's able to fend off the defender and score from 68-yards.
videos.headline: Mountaineers score on long TD pass

videos.description: Justice Hill goes right up the gut from 18 yards away and is left untouched until the celebration.
videos.headline: Hill goes untouched for second rush TD

videos.description: Will Grier notches his second touchdown throw of the day to Ka'Raun White and then converts on the two-point attempt with a nice throw to David Sills V.
videos.headline: Grier with a laser TD pass

videos.headline: Coach Gundy and Mason Rudolph excited about the offense
